children.subject: An add on to this: if you feel shaky on data structures, you can brush up by doing interview prep on data structures topics

I would say do the 2nd option: "non-academic SWE ventures" because not only is this a great and unique way to stand out on your resume but it will definitely give you more applicable experience than 61B projects in my humble opinion. I don't usually feel like I get much out of class projects because you usually have a skeleton code and tasks assigned to you to do but real life projects you don't, and thus get more out of.

history.content:
I barely passed 61b (due to not doing bearmaps, byow, and some labs but did decent on tests). 

I learned about the data structures decently enough, but just didn't have time to do lots of the assignments. I was wondering if this is really hindering my ability to be a good SWE. Would my time be best spent doing the remaining projects on 61BL or would non-academic SWE ventures be more productive?

Edit: I should mention that I'm in 61c right now and doing a great job with that.
